						<summary>

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">Chāḷukya-Vikrama year 49, Krōdhi, Vaiśākha, ba. 4, Sunday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1124, May 4, Sunday.</hi> It states that the image of Kēśavadēva was installed by some one, probably <hi rend="bold">Maiḷala [dēvi],</hi> daughter of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva,</hi> <hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> Vikramāditya VI, and wife of <hi rend="bold">Jayakēśidēva.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
